[
  {
    "start": 0,
    "end": 1.18,
    "text": "Shanghai means on the sea."
  },
  {
    "start": 1.8,
    "end": 3.3,
    "text": "Beijing, Northern capital."
  },
  {
    "start": 4,
    "end": 5.6,
    "text": "Nanjing, Southern capital."
  },
  {
    "start": 6,
    "end": 7.3,
    "text": "Chingdao, Green Island."
  },
  {
    "start": 7.8,
    "end": 9.6,
    "text": "and Hong Kong, fragrant Harbor."
  },
  {
    "start": 10.1,
    "end": 12.1,
    "text": "Because Chinese city names aren't random sounds."
  },
  {
    "start": 12.5,
    "end": 13.8,
    "text": "Everyone is a tiny description."
  },
  {
    "start": 14.1,
    "end": 15.3,
    "text": "A map you can actually read."
  },
  {
    "start": 15.9,
    "end": 19.4,
    "text": "Learn five characters from five cities and you'll never read a map the same way."
  },
  {
    "start": 19.9,
    "end": 20.4,
    "text": "Let's go."
  },
  {
    "start": 21,
    "end": 21.8,
    "text": "We start on the coast."
  },
  {
    "start": 22.1,
    "end": 23.6,
    "text": "Shanghai, Hai means sea."
  },
  {
    "start": 24,
    "end": 25.9,
    "text": "Shang means on and Hai means sea."
  },
  {
    "start": 26.5,
    "end": 28.2,
    "text": "Shanghai is literally on the sea."
  },
  {
    "start": 28.9,
    "end": 29.9,
    "text": "Exactly where it sits."
  },
  {
    "start": 30.4,
    "end": 31.4,
    "text": "at the edge of the Pacific."
  },
  {
    "start": 32,
    "end": 33.7,
    "text": "First character, Hai, sea."
  },
  {
    "start": 34.3,
    "end": 35.6,
    "text": "Now head north to the capital."
  },
  {
    "start": 36.2,
    "end": 37.7,
    "text": "Beijing, the Bay means north."
  },
  {
    "start": 38,
    "end": 40.1,
    "text": "Jing means capital and Bay means north."
  },
  {
    "start": 40.7,
    "end": 42,
    "text": "Beijing is the northern capital,"
  },
  {
    "start": 42.4,
    "end": 43.8,
    "text": "which almost asks its own question,"
  },
  {
    "start": 44.1,
    "end": 46.4,
    "text": "because if there's a northern capital, there has to be a southern one."
  },
  {
    "start": 46.9,
    "end": 48.4,
    "text": "Nanjing, Nan means south."
  },
  {
    "start": 48.8,
    "end": 49.7,
    "text": "Nan means south."
  },
  {
    "start": 50.1,
    "end": 51.6,
    "text": "Nanjing, the southern capital."
  },
  {
    "start": 52.1,
    "end": 53.9,
    "text": "Two cities, one character apart."
  },
  {
    "start": 54.4,
    "end": 55.2,
    "text": "North and south."
  },
  {
    "start": 55.6,
    "end": 56.6,
    "text": "Let's finish the compass."
  },
  {
    "start": 57,
    "end": 57.8,
    "text": "West sits Xian."
  },
  {
    "start": 58.2,
    "end": 58.9,
    "text": "She means west."
  },
  {
    "start": 59.4,
    "end": 100.5,
    "text": "And the region of Guangdong,"
  },
  {
    "start": 100.7,
    "end": 101.6,
    "text": "Dong means east."
  },
  {
    "start": 102,
    "end": 103.4,
    "text": "North, south, west, east,"
  },
  {
    "start": 103.7,
    "end": 105.6,
    "text": "all four directions straight off the map."
  },
  {
    "start": 106.1,
    "end": 108.5,
    "text": "Back to the coast and with a German surprise."
  },
  {
    "start": 109.1,
    "end": 111,
    "text": "Chingdao, Dao means island."
  },
  {
    "start": 111.6,
    "end": 114,
    "text": "Ching means green and Dao means island."
  },
  {
    "start": 114.5,
    "end": 115.4,
    "text": "The green island."
  },
  {
    "start": 116,
    "end": 117.8,
    "text": "A century ago, it was a German colony,"
  },
  {
    "start": 118,
    "end": 119.9,
    "text": "and which is why China's most famous beer,"
  },
  {
    "start": 120.3,
    "end": 120.9,
    "text": "Chingtao,"
  },
  {
    "start": 121.3,
    "end": 123.3,
    "text": "was founded right here by German brewers."
  },
  {
    "start": 123.5,
    "end": 124.8,
    "text": "Down the coast to the last one."
  },
  {
    "start": 125.1,
    "end": 125.7,
    "text": "Hong Kong."
  },
  {
    "start": 126,
    "end": 126.8,
    "text": "Gang means harbor."
  },
  {
    "start": 127.1,
    "end": 129,
    "text": "Shang means fragrant and Gang means harbor."
  },
  {
    "start": 129.6,
    "end": 130.5,
    "text": "The fragrant harbor,"
  },
  {
    "start": 130.7,
    "end": 133,
    "text": "named for the scented wood once shipped through its docks."
  },
  {
    "start": 133.4,
    "end": 137.3,
    "text": "So in five cities, sea, north, south, island, harbor,"
  },
  {
    "start": 137.5,
    "end": 139.1,
    "text": "plus west and east for free."
  },
  {
    "start": 139.8,
    "end": 140.9,
    "text": "That's the trick with Chinese."
  },
  {
    "start": 141.4,
    "end": 143.8,
    "text": "The names you half know are already teaching you the language."
  },
  {
    "start": 144.2,
    "end": 145.4,
    "text": "A map isn't just a map."
  },
  {
    "start": 145.8,
    "end": 147.1,
    "text": "It's a vocabulary list."
  },
  {
    "start": 147.6,
    "end": 149.1,
    "text": "Want to actually start learning it?"
  },
  {
    "start": 149.5,
    "end": 150.4,
    "text": "Click here to practice."
  },
  {
    "start": 150.7,
    "end": 151.5,
    "text": "Want more like this?"
  },
  {
    "start": 152,
    "end": 153,
    "text": "Follow stack tags."
  }
]